Cook ground beef and onions in a large nonstick skillet over medium high heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until no longer pink. Drain. Stir in tomatoes, mixed vegetables, Worcestershire sauce and chili sauce. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 6 to 8 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Remove from heat. Meanwhile, prepare potatoes as package directs using remaining ingredients. Drop potatoes by spoonfuls around edge of skillet.